---
---

<section id="faq" aria-labelledby="faq-heading" class="py-20 md:py-28 border-t border-[var(--c-border)]">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-8">

    <div class="reveal mb-12">
      <span class="text-[#2D5016] text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] font-medium" aria-hidden="true">FAQ</span>
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-[var(--c-text-pri)]">Common questions</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] max-w-xl">Things people ask before reaching out. If your question isn't here, just <a href="#contact" class="text-[#2D5016] hover:text-[#6B8F5E] transition-colors link-animated">contact me</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal space-y-3" role="list" aria-label="Frequently asked questions">

      <details class="group bg-[var(--c-surface)] border border-[var(--c-border)] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden" role="listitem">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer select-none list-none font-medium text-[var(--c-text-pri)] hover:text-[#2D5016] transition-colors">
          Do you do energy audits or full retrofits?
          <svg aria-hidden="true" class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <path d="M5 7.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-[var(--c-border)] pt-4">
          Both. I work at Resilient Retrofits as a sales manager under the Energy Friendly Homes (EFH) program. That means I do the initial walk-through and energy assessment, help scope the project, coordinate with licensed contractors, and manage the rebate paperwork from start to finish. If you want just an audit I can do that too — but most homeowners find it easier to have one person manage the whole job.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-[var(--c-surface)] border border-[var(--c-border)] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden" role="listitem">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer select-none list-none font-medium text-[var(--c-text-pri)] hover:text-[#2D5016] transition-colors">
          Where do you work?
          <svg aria-hidden="true" class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <path d="M5 7.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-[var(--c-border)] pt-4">
          Portland metro and Vancouver, WA — served through Resilient Retrofits. We operate under Oregon's Energy Trust (ETO) program and the Portland Clean Energy Fund (PCEF) on the Oregon side, and Clark PUD on the Washington side. If you're in the greater Portland area, we almost certainly cover you.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-[var(--c-surface)] border border-[var(--c-border)] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden" role="listitem">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer select-none list-none font-medium text-[var(--c-text-pri)] hover:text-[#2D5016] transition-colors">
          What's a heat pump going to cost me?
          <svg aria-hidden="true" class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <path d="M5 7.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-[var(--c-border)] pt-4">
          Heat pump systems run $8,500–$15,000 installed list price. Most Portland homeowners pay $3K–$7K out-of-pocket after stacking ETO, PCEF, and federal 25C credits. A free 15-minute assessment is the fastest way to get your specific number.
          <a href="#contact" class="inline-block mt-3 text-[#2D5016] font-medium hover:text-[#6B8F5E] transition-colors link-animated">Get your free assessment</a>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-[var(--c-surface)] border border-[var(--c-border)] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden" role="listitem">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer select-none list-none font-medium text-[var(--c-text-pri)] hover:text-[#2D5016] transition-colors">
          Are you available for software contract work?
          <svg aria-hidden="true" class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <path d="M5 7.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-[var(--c-border)] pt-4">
          Selectively. My strongest fit is automation work — pipelines, AI agents, overnight systems, and ServiceTitan integrations for field-service companies. I'm not a traditional freelancer taking on spec sites or design work. If you have a concrete problem that looks like "I need this system to run without me touching it every day," reach out and describe it. I'll tell you quickly whether it's a fit.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-[var(--c-surface)] border border-[var(--c-border)] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden" role="listitem">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer select-none list-none font-medium text-[var(--c-text-pri)] hover:text-[#2D5016] transition-colors">
          Do you sell the tools you build?
          <svg aria-hidden="true" class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <path d="M5 7.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-[var(--c-border)] pt-4">
          Some of them, eventually. SnuggSpec — the energy audit workflow tool — is in active development and targeting energy auditors at field-service companies as its first customer segment. Momentum Dash is a personal trading dashboard and not for sale. Other tools I build for my own workflow and open-source or write about when they're stable enough to be useful to others.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-[var(--c-surface)] border border-[var(--c-border)] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden" role="listitem">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer select-none list-none font-medium text-[var(--c-text-pri)] hover:text-[#2D5016] transition-colors">
          How do I learn what you do?
          <svg aria-hidden="true" class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <path d="M5 7.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-[var(--c-border)] pt-4">
          Two places. The <a href="/blog" class="text-[#2D5016] hover:text-[#6B8F5E] transition-colors link-animated">blog</a> is where I write about what I'm building and how — honest, in-progress posts, not polished case studies. Scraping School is a structured Python course I'm building in public — 9 modules from HTTP basics to production-grade scrapers. Module 1 through 4 are done and freely readable. Both are good starting points if you want to understand how I think about building systems.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-[var(--c-surface)] border border-[var(--c-border)] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden" role="listitem">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer select-none list-none font-medium text-[var(--c-text-pri)] hover:text-[#2D5016] transition-colors">
          What's MCP and why do you keep mentioning it?
          <svg aria-hidden="true" class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <path d="M5 7.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-[var(--c-border)] pt-4">
          MCP stands for Model Context Protocol — it's Anthropic's open standard for connecting AI models like Claude to external tools and data sources. In practice, it's how I give Claude the ability to call APIs, read files, run code, and take real actions in external systems without me writing a new integration for every tool. It's a big deal for automation work because it dramatically expands what an AI agent can actually do. I write about it on the blog if you want the longer version.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-[var(--c-surface)] border border-[var(--c-border)] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden" role="listitem">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 cursor-pointer select-none list-none font-medium text-[var(--c-text-pri)] hover:text-[#2D5016] transition-colors">
          Do you take on apprentices or mentees?
          <svg aria-hidden="true" class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <path d="M5 7.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[var(--c-text-sec)] text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-[var(--c-border)] pt-4">
          Not formally, but I'm open to it for the right person. My time is limited — I have a full-time day job and several active builds running in parallel. What I can offer is honest, direct feedback on your work, occasional pairing sessions on automation or scraping projects, and access to how I actually structure my builds. If you're self-directed, already shipping things, and not looking for hand-holding, reach out with what you're working on.
        </div>
      </details>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

